.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jan 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-test - Run a diagnostic test for a specific service


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel test [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
This command runs a pre-defined suite of mock jobs against a newly provisioned
service to ensure it is working correctly. It is typically called automatically
by 'init --test'.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for test

.PP
\fB--service\fP=""
	The service to run tests for (e.g., vllm, ollama)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--auth-service\fP="https://aceteam.ai"
	The URL of the authentication service

.PP
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is $HOME/.citadel-cli.yaml)

.PP
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--nexus\fP="https://nexus.aceteam.ai"
	The URL of the AceTeam Nexus server


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
